{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/history/past-prime-ministers/frederick-north","content_id":"ec2710bb-102b-43e1-9aa5-1df3f0f7466a","description":"“Men may be popular without being ambitious, but there is hardly an ambitious man who does not try to be popular.”\r\n","details":{"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Lord North was long regarded as a failure as Prime Minister due to his association with Britain’s catastrophic defeat in the American War of Independence (1775 to 1783). He was also condemned by opponents as complicit in a reassertion of royal power against Parliament. However Lord North is more justly appreciated as an outstanding parliamentarian and potentially great premier brought low, like so many others, by ‘events’.</p>\n\n<p>Read more about Lord Frederick North on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://history.blog.gov.uk/2015/08/12/lord-frederick-north/\" class=\"govuk-link\">History of government blog.</a></p>\n</div>","born":"13 April 1732, Piccadilly, London","dates_in_office":[{"end_year":1782,"start_year":1770}],"died":"5 August 1792, London","interesting_facts":"North was in office when the United States of America declared independence.","major_acts":"Tea Act 1773: which sparked the Boston Tea party and led to the American Revolution in 1776.","political_party":"Tory"},"document_type":"historic_appointment","first_published_at":"2023-01-19T17:38:35+00:00","links":{"available_translations":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/history/past-prime-ministers/frederick-north","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/history/past-prime-ministers/frederick-north","base_path":"/government/history/past-prime-ministers/frederick-north","content_id":"ec2710bb-102b-43e1-9aa5-1df3f0f7466a","document_type":"historic_appointment","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2023-01-19T17:38:35Z","schema_name":"historic_appointment","title":"Lord Frederick North","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/history/past-prime-mini